cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a machine learning method for separating mixed distributions, which is a common problem in various fields such as signal processing and image/audio separation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development and application of machine learning algorithms. The paper also involves signal processing, which falls under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.SI (Image and Video Processing). Additionally, the experiments involve image and audio separation, which are relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
